&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;The Financial Analyst plays a key role in global financial planning and analysis, including budgeting,&amp;nbsp;forecasting, reporting and financial modeling. This role partners closely with internal departments and&amp;nbsp;international subsidiaries to deliver insights that inform business decisions and drive financial results, with&amp;nbsp;an emphasis on the International Distributor channel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Description&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Works with department leadership to plan, execute, and analyze the global forecasting process for International Distributors, including long-range plan, budget, forecasts, guidance, and monthly reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Produce monthly management reporting packages, dashboards and presentations for senior management and other stakeholders, translating&amp;nbsp;complex data into actionable insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Researches and answers questions and recommends solutions to problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Conduct detailed analysis of financial statements, historical data, and market trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Partner across functions and global subsidiaries to assess financial impacts and inform decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Build and maintain financial models, analyses, and dashboards to support strategic initiatives and assessments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Maintain the Adaptive Planning system, ensuring data accuracy, supporting reporting needs, and assisting users with system functionality and issue&amp;nbsp;resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
