&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;The Finance Systems &amp;amp; AI Enablement Manager maintains the technical infrastructure supporting&amp;nbsp;KEEN&#39;s global Financial Planning &amp;amp; Analysis (FP&amp;amp;A) function. This includes supporting financial&amp;nbsp;systems, preparation of global consolidated reporting, and developing AI-driven workflows across the&amp;nbsp;Finance department. The position ensures that the systems, data, and consolidated reports used by the&amp;nbsp;FP&amp;amp;A team and executive leadership are accurate, timely, and progressively automated. This role will&amp;nbsp;serve as an advanced resource for the new AI Center of Excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Description&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Financial Systems &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Serve as an advanced finance systems resource for KEEN’s core&amp;nbsp;financial planning, reporting, and consolidation systems, including SAP, Adaptive Analytics, and related FP&amp;amp;A data flows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Support system configuration, user provisioning, security access, metadata updates, release testing, and ongoing system enhancements in partnership with Finance, Accounting, and GBT stakeholders.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Maintain and update financial system structures, including chart of&amp;nbsp;accounts, organizational hierarchies, cost centers, reporting&amp;nbsp;dimensions, allocation rules, and integration mappings between SAP&amp;nbsp;and the planning platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Provide functional support to global finance users across regions by&amp;nbsp;troubleshooting data, calculation, reporting, and access issues during close, forecast, budget, and Long Range Plan cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Support the SAP S/4HANA implementation and cutover for finance planning and reporting processes by gathering requirements, developing test scenarios, validating data during parallel runs, and assisting with post-go-live stabilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Document system configuration, data flows, standard operating&amp;nbsp;procedures, and process changes to support consistent system&amp;nbsp;usage and reporting practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consolidation &amp;amp; Financial Reporting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Lead the preparation of monthly, quarterly, and annual consolidated&amp;nbsp;financial reporting across KEEN regions, channels, and reporting&amp;nbsp;entities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Execute and review multi-currency consolidation activities, including&amp;nbsp;foreign exchange translation, constant-currency reporting,&amp;nbsp;intercompany eliminations, and reconciliation between local-currency&amp;nbsp;and U.S. dollar reporting views.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Prepare consolidated reporting packages for actuals close, forecasts, budget, Long Range Plan, and group reporting using&amp;nbsp;standardized reporting and variance analysis views.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Analyze and validate consolidated revenue, gross margin, OPEX, Operating Income, and non-financial KPI reporting to support&amp;nbsp;accuracy, consistency, and timely decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Partner with Accounting, Treasury, regional finance teams, and other stakeholders to resolve reporting issues, improve data quality, and&amp;nbsp;support timely close and planning processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Apply KEEN’s KPI definitions, reporting hierarchies, and consolidation standards consistently across recurring financial&amp;nbsp;reporting deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Identify and recommend process improvements to enhance reporting accuracy

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inventory Control Clerk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1st Shift&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Inventory Control Clerk is responsible for maintaining inventory records, preparing and processing cycle counts, compiling and distributing specified reporting, velocity research and slotting and helping to balance WMI and SAP. The Inventory Control Clerk is a valued member of the KEEN Fan Engagement Center (FEC) family.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scope and Complexity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advanced and complicated tasks requiring considerable judgment, independent analysis and detailed knowledge of the position and procedures. May provide guidance to lower-level employees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Researches and documents root cause of inventory discrepancies. Ensures system count matches physical inventory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Updates WMS to match physical through various methods. Inputs required data elements into WMS and various other applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data setup and validation. Audits existing data for inaccuracies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documents information on product hold and inspections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviews standard operating procedures and keeps documentation current.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works with inventory department management to document and train warehouse operations staff on inventory procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists with daily and weekly reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists in development and implementation of special projects and tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports operations through building wide housekeeping maintenance including cardboard and waste removal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Moves labor to balance building workload within the building.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributes to a positive work environment in a manner that is consistent with KEEN expectations; Provides outstanding service to our partners and fans. Promotes a safety-first work environment. Shows respect for the KEEN brand; including teammates within the operation. Conducts self with reliable and punctual attendance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum two (2) years of work experience in a distribution center or warehouse environment. Experience in inventory control preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate material handling equipment as needed and obtain any required certifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to solve problems with high energy and a positive attitude.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills with the ability to communicate at all levels of the organization and with external partners.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to positively lead and staff associate team members to accomplish daily, weekly and monthly production goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a warehouse environment (e.g., hot summers, cold winters).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to stand for long periods of time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift/move up to 50 pounds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: Order Processing Associate - MHE&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to: Operations Supervisor&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Status: Full - Time, Non Exempt&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift: 2nd&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Order Processing Associates – MHE are a vital part of the KEEN Team and one of the most common entry points into our Distribution Center (DC) team. These positions support the RF picking and RF packing of all outbound orders at the DC. The primary focus of the Order Processing Associate is to move product accurately and efficiently throughout the DC. Associates will be operating powered equipment such as order pickers, pallet riders and reach trucks depending on the needs of the Operation. Associates will work in multiple areas as assigned and support areas based on business volume and team performance. Associates will model KEEN values and act in accordance with KEEN’s mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operates power equipment to support inbound putaway, replenishment, and pick process using powered equipment for the majority of scheduled shift.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepares orders for shipment, by picking, sorting, and packing product accurately and timely.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works in multiple departments; requiring different task actions, lifting requirements, and technology tools such as RF scanning equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifies and reports problems and supports solutions to maintain excellent service and quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports DC operations through building wide housekeeping maintenance including cardboard and waste removal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Builds rapport with other departments to ensure correct order flow, service levels and quality levels are maintained.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively and safely operates various types of powered material handling equipment to complete assigned tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Moves to work within the DC as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributes to a positive work environment in a manner that is consistent with KEEN values and expectations; with the bottom line expectation of providing outstanding service to KEEN retail partners and fans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shows respect for the KEEN brand and teammates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On time and reliable; meets or exceeds attendance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Physical/Mental Requirements:&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to frequently lift and shift boxes weighing an average of 30 to 40 pounds with a maximum of 65 pounds throughout a full shift of work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work in a standing or walking environment for 8-10 hour shifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to cross train in other departments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to comprehend and apply Standard Operating Procedures (SOP’s).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preferred 2+ years’ experience operating powered equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete onsite training and certification on order picker, reach truck, sit down, and electric pallet jack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be at least 18 years old&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willing and able to work extended shifts extra days as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;May be required to work overtime&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to read and take direction in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successful completion of 60-day training program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;

