&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;The Senior Global Product Line Manager (PLM) manages the global PLM function for the organization&amp;nbsp;and is responsible for the integration of fan, market, channel, assortment, segmentation, competitor,&amp;nbsp;product trend and lifecycle analysis and sales data to drive vision via seasonal product collections that&amp;nbsp;achieve defined business and product strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Description&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plans and leads the briefing of innovative, opinion-leading, commercial and&amp;nbsp;brand-enhancing global product lines designed for global and regional fans&amp;nbsp;that deliver revenue, MSRP, margin, profitability, productivity, color/material&amp;nbsp;guidance, construction, lifecycle targets, channel segmentation plans and&amp;nbsp;other metrics as required. Provides input on seasonal global and regional&amp;nbsp;analysis to inform the global briefing process. Synthesizes findings and&amp;nbsp;inputs including but not limited to: product performance, assortment&amp;nbsp;performance by channel/tier/key account/DTC, competitor analysis, trend&amp;nbsp;reports, fan insights, market research data, retail visits, brand strength, trade&amp;nbsp;publications and analysts, the executive team, and regional and global&amp;nbsp;business units.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Works cross-functionally throughout the seasonal product process with the&amp;nbsp;Lifestyle and Performance business units to bring a cohesive, cross-&amp;nbsp;merchandised, fan-focused line with compelling stories each season&amp;nbsp;delivered on-time and completely.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Executes against long-term and in-season strategic initiatives via the global&amp;nbsp;product line plan and seasonal briefing as determined by senior&amp;nbsp;management and merchandising analytics. Supports continuous&amp;nbsp;improvement on style/sku efficiency, margins, regional alignment and other&amp;nbsp;key metrics as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Supports regional fan and channel needs with specific inline and regionally&amp;nbsp;driven styles as required by the business (SMU’s, limited editions,&amp;nbsp;collaborations, exclusive product).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Manages and monitors new product introductions and carryover to ensure&amp;nbsp;successful planned launch and/or lifecycle. Provides clear and effective&amp;nbsp;cross-functional communication around the product line at key calendar&amp;nbsp;checkpoints, meetings and product presentations as required (oral and&amp;nbsp;written). Aligns and motivates the product team to deliver product lines with&amp;nbsp;compelling stories for both new and carryover styles that drive brand&amp;nbsp;awareness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Supports successful sell-in and sell-through of the seasonal product line via&amp;nbsp;close collaboration, communication and product data accuracy with various&amp;nbsp;internal groups throughout the concept-to-fan/go-to-market process to&amp;nbsp;deliver against seasonal targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Supports global product creation and sell-in strategies with the necessary&amp;nbsp;administrative tools, including but not limited to: product briefs, visual line&amp;nbsp;plans, product descriptions, fan insights, tech sheets, packaging direction,&amp;nbsp;product training information and other tools as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Presents pre-lines, sales meetings, key accounts, and visiting editors as&amp;nbsp;required with sales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Serves as point of contact for all product line activities or inquiries from&amp;nbsp;consumer service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
